-- Allium Medical Climbs Most in Three Weeks on Gardia Acquisition
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-01-30T09:36:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/allium-medical-climbs-most-in-three-weeks-on-gardia-acquisition.html
Allium Medical Solutions Ltd. (ALMD)  rose
the most in three weeks in  Tel Aviv  after the developer of
removable stents said it will buy Gardia Medical Ltd.  The  shares  advanced 5.1 percent, the biggest intraday jump
since Jan. 9, to 0.675 shekel, at 11:24 a.m. in Tel Aviv, giving
the Caesarea, Israel-based company a market value of 98 million
shekels ($26 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
